Personal data processing may only be processed with the express consent of the data subject. The data subject may withdraw his/her consent at any time.&nbsp;
However, in some cases, consent is not required if the processing is necessary.&nbsp;
The person concerned by the collection of their data has a right to information, a right of access, a right of rectification and a right to object to their data being collected.Last modified 22 Dec 2021
				
			